# OOP Assignments in Python

This folder contains 21 Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) assignments implemented in Python.

## List of Assignments
1. Using self
2. Using cls
3. Public Variables and Methods
4. Class Variables and Class Methods
5. Static Variables and Static Methods
6. Constructors and Destructors
7. Access Modifiers: Public, Private, and Protected
8. The super() Function
9. Abstract Classes and Methods
10. Instance Methods
11. Class Methods
12. Static Methods
13. Composition
14. Aggregation
15. Method Resolution Order (MRO) and Diamond Inheritance
16. Function Decorators
17. Class Decorators
18. Property Decorators: @property, @setter, and @deleter
19. callable() and __call__()
20. Creating a Custom Exception
21. Make a Custom Class Iterable

## How to Run

1. Make sure Python 3 is installed on your system.
2. Open terminal or VS Code.
3. Open the assignment file you want to run.
4. Run the file using the command:

python filename.py

Example:
python assignment1_self.py
.....assigment2 ,3,4 etc


. The output will be shown in the terminal.

---

Enjoy learning OOP with these assignments!


